item.title: Initial Post
item.description: Welcome to my blog! I plan to use this site to share my projects and code with the world, and may occasionally speak to other interests of mine.

item.title: About Me
item.description: I am an undergraduate computer science student at the University of Notre Dame graduating in 2022. Outside of my studies I spend much of my time at the pool playing for the Notre Dame men’s water polo team. Originally, I am from the Bellevue/Eastside area of Seattle, where I attended Eastside Catholic School and graduated in 2018. I am also a proud alumni of the Bellevue Club Swim Team, where I swam for Klaas, Andrew, Dwight, Lee, and Ash since 9 years old until I graduated high school.

item.title: Contact Me
item.description: Get In Touch Feel free to get in touch with me! Email: dane_williams@outlook.com I am happy to talk about projects or anything for that matter. Please note that the email I have provided is my personal email which I don’t always check regularly. Normally, I respond to emails within a couple of days, but it’s always possible that you catch me during midterms week and I am a bit slower.
